pageContext.claim: “As you saw yesterday, that whole nonsense ended with a very poor performance by a man named Robert Mueller, an incompetent performance, but they say a lot of it started with Ukraine.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that Ukraine played a role in starting the probe that led to the investigation by special counsel Robert Mueller. While ledgers were disclosed that showed $12.7 million in payments from a Russia-linked Ukrainian party to Trump campaign chairman Paul Manafort, forcing him to resign, that happened after the FBI had opened the investigation.
